# Commit messages

Headline:

- Imperative mood. "Add", "Fix", "Remove", "Rewrite", "Bump".
- No trailing period.
- Aim for under 72 characters. Hard cap at 80.

Body (optional, include only when the headline isn't self-evident):

- Separate from the headline with one blank line.
- Default to one short paragraph (2-3 sentences); reach for more only
  when the *why* genuinely warrants it.
- Plain prose, not a bullet dump.
- Explain the *why*, not the *what* (the diff already shows the what).
- Obey the typography rules from `typography.mdc`.
